
[1]intolerant

   INTOL'ERANT, a. [L. in and tolero, to endure.]

   1. Not enduring; not able to endure.

   The powers of the human body being limited and intolerant of excesses.

   2. Not enduring difference of opinion or worship; refusing to tolerate
   others in the enjoyment of their opinions, rights and worship.

             INTOL'ERANT, n. One who does not favor toleration.
